/* Flex Container Properties */
display: flex;     -Defines a flex container and enables flex context for all its direct children.

flex-direction     -Defines the direction of the main axis (horizontal or vertical).
Values: row (default), row-reverse, column, column-reverse.

flex-wrap          -Controls whether the flex items should wrap or not.
Values: nowrap (default), wrap, wrap-reverse.

justify-content    -Aligns flex items along the main axis.
Values: flex-start (default), flex-end, center, space-between, space-around, space-evenly.

align-items        -Aligns flex items along the cross axis.
Values: stretch (default), flex-start, flex-end, center, baseline.

align-content      -Aligns flex lines when there is extra space in the cross axis.
Values: stretch (default), flex-start, flex-end, center, space-between, space-around.

gap                -Defines the space between flex items.
Values: normal (default), <length> (px, em, rem, etc.), <percentage>.




/* Flex Item Properties */
order             -Controls the order of the flex items.
Values: <integer> (default is 0).


align-self         -Allows the default alignment (or the one specified by align-items) to be overridden for individual flex items.
Values: auto (default), flex-start, flex-end, center, baseline, stretch.


flex              -Shorthand for flex-grow, flex-shrink, and flex-basis properties.
Values: none (default), <flex-grow> <flex-shrink> <flex-basis>.
Default value is 0 1 auto.

    flex-grow     -Defines the ability for a flex item to grow if necessary.
    Values: 0 (default), 1, 2.

    flex-shrink   -Defines the ability for a flex item to shrink if necessary.
    Default value is 1.

    flex-basis    -Defines the default size of an element before the remaining space is distributed.
    Default value is auto.

Examples of flex property values:
    *flex: 0;               --makes children take up only the space they need
    flex: 1;                --makes children take up equal space
    flex: 2;                --makes children take up twice as much space as other children

    flex: 0 0 200px;        --makes children take up 200px of space
    flex: 1 0 200px;        --makes children take up 200px of space, but can grow if needed
    flex: 1 1 200px;        --makes children take up 200px of space, but can shrink if needed